Dataset:  ydata-video2gif-v1_0

===========================================================================
Yahoo! Video2GIF dataset, version 1.0

The Video2GIF dataset contains the IDs and URLs of over 100'000 GIFs and their source video.
The GIFs are collected from GIF websites (makeagif.com, gifsoup.com) in Summer 2015.
The source videos were collected from YouTube.
In addition the dataset contains the 357 videos of the test set, which are licenced
under Creative Commons (CC-BY) license. 
The dataset shall be used to evaluate video highlight and GIF creation techniques.

If you end up using the dataset, we ask you to cite the following paper:

    Michael Gygli, Yale Song, Liangliang Cao
    "Video2GIF: Automatic Generation of Animated GIFs from Video," IEEE CVPR 2016

If you have any question regarding the dataset, please contact:

    Michael Gygli <gygli@vision.ee.ethz.ch>

===========================================================================
This dataset is provided as part of the Yahoo! Webscope program, to be
used for approved non-commercial research purposes by recipients who 
have signed a Data Sharing Agreement with Yahoo!. This dataset is not
to be redistributed. No personally identifying information is available
in this dataset. More information about the Yahoo! Webscope program is
available at http://research.yahoo.com

===========================================================================

Full description:

This dataset contains one zip-compressed archive file.

The content of the file is as follows:


(a) "metadata.txt" This files contains the information on the GIFs, their corresponding source video ID and the temporal alignement of the GIF to the video.
    Furthermore it contains meta information such as the number of views per GIF and video.
    The format is as follows:

(b) "video_tags" A file containing a list of video tags for each video. The tags on line "n" corresponds to the video on line "n" in metadata.txt

(c) "testset.txt" Contains the YouTubeIDs of the videos used to evaluate our method

(d) "./test_videos/" this directory contains the 357 test videos, which are licenced under Creative Commons (CC-BY).
    Their format is: YouTubeID.mp4

(e) "./evaluation/" This directory contains evaluation code for nMSD and Average Precision (in python)
    Requires the packages 'numpy', 'scikit-learn' and 'pandas' which can be installed using pip

Last edit: March 10, 2016
